# Always Benchmark with Multi-Replica Cluster

When running benchmarks on kind or any k8s deployment, ALWAYS use at least
3 replicas (the default in `deploy/kind/dex-values-kind.yaml`).

## Rules

- **NEVER** reduce to 1 replica to "simplify" debugging — single-replica hides
  critical cluster routing bugs (tasklist partition forwarding, shard
  cross-node dispatch, heartbeat forwarding, etc.).
- When debugging cluster issues, check logs on **ALL** nodes, not just one.
- Use `deploy/scripts/benchmark-escalation.sh` to run benchmarks — it triggers
  with fire-and-forget (`wait=false`) and polls the DB directly for completion.
  Never use `wait=true` on the benchmark trigger API.
